<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-04-07T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-04-07T13:00:00-05:00" n="226" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d226">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">814.51/281: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-04-07T14:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">April 7,
                                            1919, 2 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>Referring to your telegram of March 29, 6 P.M. and 9 P.M.<note n="7" xml:id="d226fn7">Latter not printed.</note> Inform Catlin that
                                in accordance with its usual policy the Government of the United
                                States would give all proper diplomatic support to any legitimate
                                enterprise of this character to which its citizens are parties if
                                beneficial to Guatemala and its citizens.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>